#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:1
msgid "Cargo workspaces for multi-package projects"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.12](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.12-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:5
msgid "Cargo used to have two levels of organization:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:7
msgid "A _package_ contains one or more crates"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:8
msgid "A crate has one or more modules"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:10
msgid "Cargo now has an additional level:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:12
msgid "A _workspace_ contains one or more packages"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:14
msgid ""
"This can be useful for larger projects. For example, [the `futures` package]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/futures-rs) is a _workspace_ that "
"contains many related packages:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:17
msgid "futures"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:18
msgid "futures-util"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:19
msgid "futures-io"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:20
msgid "futures-channel"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:22
msgid "and more."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:26
msgid ""
"Workspaces allow these packages to be developed individually, but they share "
"a single set of dependencies, and therefore have a single target directory "
"and a single `Cargo.lock`."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:30
msgid ""
"For more details about workspaces, please see [the Cargo documentation]"
"(https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/cargo/reference/manifest.html#the-"
"workspace-section)."
msgstr ""
